# Error Throw Block Style

For readability and clarity, never use one-line `if` + `throw` statements.

Use explicit block form with braces and line breaks.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
if (error) throw new Error(error.message)
```

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
if (error) {
  throw new Error(error.message);
}
```

Apply this rule consistently in all JS/TS code, including API modules, hooks, components, and utilities.

